1. Cut with a knife and fill geometry (like F)
-> knife-bisect + fill + clear inner/outer (F - change knife direction)

2. Triangulate faces
-> up menu 'face' 
-> triangulate faces (Ctrl + T)

3. Create a new object by exist geometry
-> select target geometry 
-> shift + D + right click
-> P + selection

4. Fix for 'scale'
-> Ctrl + A 
-> scale

5. Fix faces orientation 
-> Edit mode
-> Alt + N
-> recalculate outside

6. Add a tree
-> edit
-> preferences
-> add-ons (add curve - sapling tree gen)
-> Shift + A (curve - sapling tree gen)

7. Using Alpha channel
-> Material properties (settings)
-> blend mode - alpha blend 
-> use alpha channel on nodes

8. scattering
-> add particle (hair) 
-> render - select instance object 
-> add new vertex groupe to object
-> go to weight paint mode 
-> add vertex group to particle system

9. Run difference boolean operation
-> addOn Bool Tool enablen (?)
-> Ctrl + 'Num-'

10. Connect two parralel faces (hole)
-> addOn Loop Tools enablen
-> select faces
-> right click (Loop Tools)
-> Loop Tools (bridge)

11. Bind parameter to frame
-> #frame/35 

12. UV mapping
-> U + 'Mark seam'
-> add test image texture and use Ctrl + L (link materials) for check result




















